-- Top New York Fed official Sack to resign this month
-- 
-- Fri Jan 4, 2013 4:25pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/04/us-usa-fed-sack-idUSBRE9030UL20130104

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Brian Sack, formerly head of the Federal Reserve Bank of New York's open market operations who for the last six months served as a senior policy advisor, is to resign effective January 18. 
 In a statement, the New York Fed said Sack announced his intention to resign. Sack oversaw the U.S. central bank's market-based monetary policy actions, including its quantitative easing programs, from June, 2009 through June, 2012. He has since advised New York Fed President William Dudley. (Reporting by  Jonathan Spicer ; Editing by  Chizu Nomiyama )